Naididae
). The determination of the biomass of these small and quickly desiccated worms is very difficult. Therefore, the following procedure was performed: some of the larger individuals (especially adult worms of the genus 

Guaranidrilus

) were weighed directly. The biomass of other enchytraeid species was estimated by using values previously determined for European species of similar size (
Römbke & Kreysch 1988
).

